<div class="container" id='content'>

  <div class="row-fluid styleguide-notes">
    <div class="styleguide-wrapper">
      <p>Successful order confirmation</p>
      <hr />
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- Sample code here -->

  <div class="confirmation-message-container success">
    <div class="confirmation-heading">
      <h1>Thank you, your order is confirmed</h1>
      <p class='order-reference'>Order No: <span class="ref">5000235689</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="confirmation-summary">
      <p>Check your email where your order confirmation will be sent shortly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Sample code ends -->


  <div class="row-fluid styleguide-notes">
    <div class="styleguide-wrapper">
      <p>Failed order confirmation</p>
      <hr />
    </div>
  </div>

    <!-- Sample code here -->

  <div class="confirmation-message-container failure">
    <div class="confirmation-heading">
      <h1>Unfortunately there has been a problem with your order</h1>
      <p class='order-reference'>Order No: <span class="ref">5000235689</span></p>
    </div>
    <div class="confirmation-summary">
      <p>We were unable to process your order</p>
      <p><a href="">Generic call to action message</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Sample code ends -->
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- Style guide notes go here -->

  <div class="row-fluid styleguide-notes">

    <div class="styleguide-wrapper">
      <div class="span12">
        <div class="content-container styleguide-container">
          <h1>Styleguide notes</h1>
          <hr />
          <h2>Order confirmation - checkout</h2>
          <hr />

          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>The confirmation message describes the state of the checkout process after completion. This will either be a failure or success. </p>
            <h4>Interactions</h4>
            <p>A user can link to their Clubcard account. Presumably this prompts a login if user is not already signed in. </p>
            <h4>Layout modes</h4>
            <p>There is only a single layout mode for this component.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <p>Only common styles are loaded for this component.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common-components/confirmation.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>The confirmation can come in two states. Success or Failure. Dummy content is provided for both panels. A call to action can be added to the Failure panel if required</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

